#Text=Nigerian man charged with trying to blow up airliner
#Text=Sunday , December 27 , 2009
#Text=A Northwest Airbus A330 with Delta Air Lines livery ( Delta and Northwest have merged ) , similar to the one involved in the incident aboard Flight 253 .
#Text=Image : Gietje .
#Text=U.S. authorities have charged Nigerian Umar Farouk Abdulmutallab with trying to blow up a plane on its descent into the city of Detroit , Michigan on Friday .
#Text=The man , who comes from a prominent Nigerian family , was read the charges in a hospital Saturday , where he is being treated for burns .
#Text=The charges were read by United States District Judge Paul Borman while Abdulmutallab was being held at the University of Michigan Medical Center in Ann Arbor , Michigan .
#Text=Abdulmutallab was asked if he understood the charges against him , and he answered in English that he did .
#Text=Witnesses reported he was in a wheelchair with a blanket over his lap .
#Text=The U.S. government accuses the Nigerian national of bringing an explosive device onto Friday 's Northwest Airlines Flight 253 plane from Amsterdam in the Netherlands .
#Text=A preliminary analysis by federal authorities indicates he used a syringe to detonate a highly explosive substance , identified as PETN .
#Text=Abdulmutallab said he got the explosives in Yemen from an Al Qaeda bomb maker who sewed the device into his underwear .
#Text=Passengers have told investigators the man went into the bathroom for 20 minutes before landing and complained about stomach problems before pulling a blanket on himself .
#Text=Just as the plane was getting ready to land , they heard a pop , smelled smoke and then saw the man on fire .
#Text=A Dutch passenger , Jasper Schuringa , jumped on the Nigerian to subdue him , and a fire extinguisher was used to put out the fire .
#Text=The House Committee on Homeland Security chairman , Bennie Thompson , said it was a very close call .
#Text=" We 're just fortunate nothing happened .

#Text=Meanwhile , security screening measures have upgraded in the wake of the foiled attack , including only allowing one carry-on bag for international passengers , banning anyone from moving around the airplane during the last hour of the flight and additional  unpredictable " measures that will vary from airport to airport .
